verbs.description: emmantle (third-person singular simple present emmantles, present participle emmantling, simple past and past participle emmantled)

examples: The World, and this, which by another name men have thought good to call Heaven (under the pourprise and bending cope wherof, all things are emmanteled and covered) beleeve wee ought in all reason to be a God, eternall, unmeasurable, without beginning, and likewise endlesse.
